either, motherfucker.

44:01.754 --> 44:05.055
All right, cowboy, look.
Jump in the middle.

44:10.695 --> 44:12.628
It's real simple.

44:12.630 --> 44:15.431
When both ears pointing
one way, to the front,

44:15.433 --> 44:17.332
he's happy.

44:17.334 --> 44:19.635
When they're both pointing
to the back, he ain't so happy.

44:19.637 --> 44:21.236
You see his ears?

44:21.238 --> 44:23.672
Well, just tell me
what to do, all right?

44:23.674 --> 44:26.542
You got to be patient, man.

44:26.544 --> 44:30.213
You got to be patient if you
want to get your hands on him.

44:34.017 --> 44:36.216
It's a real nice horse
you got here, man.

44:36.218 --> 44:38.286
What'd you name him?

44:38.288 --> 44:39.787
I haven't named him yet.

44:39.789 --> 44:42.522
Everybody need a name, Roman.

44:42.524 --> 44:45.595
It might be the reason he's not
coming when you call him.

44:49.766 --> 44:54.366
I read something about a guy
who could gallop so slow

44:54.368 --> 44:57.172
it took him an hour
to go 300 yards.

44:59.040 --> 45:00.473
That's the whole story?

45:00.475 --> 45:02.041
That's slower
than that mule over there.

45:02.043 --> 45:03.342
- That's very unimpressive.
- No, no, no.

45:03.344 --> 45:05.979
It's about
controlling strength.

45:07.816 --> 45:10.749
